com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.canAddPass(.methodDes: Checks whether the type of pass can be added.

params.appid: Mandatory. App ID applied for on the HUAWEI Developers website
params.passType: Mandatory. Pass type, which uniquely maps to the app ID and is obtained during pass service application on the HUAWEI Developers website

com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.addPass(jav.methodDes: Adds a pass to HUAWEI Wallet, which will verify the signature of the pass.

params.hwPassData: Mandatory. Base64-encoded pass package to be added

com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.requireAcce.methodDes: Requests to modify the token of a pass (for NFC card only). Upon successful request, a one-time token with a validity period will be returned.

params.passTypeId: Pass type ID entered during pass service application on the HUAWEI Developers website

com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.requireAcce.methodDes: Requests a temporary public key for communicating with the NFC card. Before making the request, obtain the token for interacting with the NFC card. Then, include the token in the signature for request verification.

params.sign: Certificate-based signature for the string of pass type ID, pass ID, and access token. The access token should be obtained by calling the token application API

com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.modifyNFCCa.methodDes: Modifies parameters of a pass (NFC card only). Before calling this API, obtain the temporary public key for communicating with the NFC card and encrypt the request parameters.

params.cardParams: Pass parameters (in JSON format) to be modified. The key of each parameter should be specified during card application on the HUAWEI Developers website, while the value of the parameter should be encrypted by using tempAccessSec, the temporary public key for communicating with the card. Note: For details about the format of the cardParams parameter, please refer to the blank card format requirements
params.reason: Reason for card writing. This parameter is optional for the initial API call but is mandatory for subsequent updates. A dialog should be displayed for the user to acknowledge card writing
params.sign: Certificate-based signature for the string of pass type ID, pass ID, card parameters, reason, and access token
params.callBack: Callback function that is used after the pass modification API is called, through which the callback result will be returned asynchronously

com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.readNFCCard.methodDes: Queries designated parameters of a pass (NFC card only). The request should contain the specified temporary public key for encrypting the query result.

params.cardParams: The value adopts the following format: car_key_sn: , car_key_group: , read_publickey: Temporary public key that is passed to the API, for encrypting the query result. Mandatory.After obtaining the parameters, fill the card serial number in car_key_sn and the key group number in car_key_group (separate multiple key group numbers with vertical bars (|). Then, encrypt the entire string using the public key in read_publickey
params.reason: Reason for the query. This field is reserved and can be left empty
params.sign: Certificate-based signature for the string of pass type ID, pass ID, card parameters, reason, and access token

com.hw.passsdk.WalletPassApi.deletePass(.methodDes: Deletes a pass based on PassId.

params.sign: Certificate-based signature for the string of pass type ID and pass ID
